
[1]designation

   DESIGNATION, n.

   1. The act of pointing or marking out by signs or objects; as the
   designation of an estate by boundaries.

   2. Indication; a showing or pointing; a distinguishing from others.

   3. Appointment; direction; as, a claim to a throne grounded on the
   designation of a predecessor.

   4. Appointment; a selecting and appointing; assignment; as the
   designation of an officer to a particular command.

   5. Import; distinct application.

   Finite and infinite are primarily attributed in their first designation
   to things which have parts.
